    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "~The problem is that for the moment InstantSearch.js only stores search related parameters in the URL and since it's a direct mapping of the internal state (only search related), it means some deep modifications.~\r\n\r\n~We can add the API proposed by @julienpa but that's external thus this will force the developer to do the integration themselves, which can be tricky.~\r\n\r\nMy bad I misread the expected behavior, it's based on wether or not it's refined so it should be ok. We're gonna try to integrate soon :)",
